import pandas as pd
from datetime import timedelta

# Load CSV
df = pd.read_csv('/workspace/april-attendance-data.csv')
# Strip spaces in column names
df.columns = [c.strip() for c in df.columns]
# Parse datetime
# Combine Date and times to full datetime
# Some times may be like '08:52' - assume same day

df['Clock-in_dt'] = pd.to_datetime(df['Date'].str.strip() + ' ' + df['Clock-in'].str.strip(), format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M')
df['Clock-out_dt'] = pd.to_datetime(df['Date'].str.strip() + ' ' + df['Clock-out'].str.strip(), format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M')
# Compute duration

df['Duration'] = df['Clock-out_dt'] - df['Clock-in_dt']
# Identify employees who worked more than 9.5 hours (9.5*60=570 minutes)
threshold = pd.Timedelta(hours=9.5)
long_workers = df.groupby('Name')['Duration'].max()
long_workers = long_workers[long_workers > threshold]
long_worker_names = list(long_workers.index)
len(long_worker_names), long_worker_names[:10]
